wikipedia_page.main: Lieutenant Walbanke Ashby Pritt,  (31 January 1897 – 27 January 1928) was a British First World War flying ace credited with five aerial victories.

response: *Walbanke Ashby Pritt – British World War I flying ace credited with five aerial victories. He flew with the Royal Flying Corps in 1917/1918; flying Sopwith Pups.
